text: Springfield is a city in southwestern Ohio. At the 2020 United States Census, 58,662 people lived there. It is the county seat of Clark County. The city was founded in 1801. It was incorporated in 1827 as a village, and as a city in 1850. == References == Category:Cities in Ohio Category:County seats in Ohio Category:1801 establishments in the United States Category:1800s establishments in Ohio
title: Springfield, Ohio
